'''1707'''
* ''s.d.''{{snd}}''s.d.'': Joseph de Aguilar (forcibly) resettles Tipuans to Nojpeten during a {{lang|es|reducción}}.{{sfn|Jones|1989|pp=270–272}}{{sfn|Gerhard|1979|p=74}}{{sfn|Jones|1998|pp=408–412}}<ref group=note>See 1703 Hon maps of Maya groups Link: https://lccn.loc.gov/99446135 / https://lccn.loc.gov/2010587361 / https://lccn.loc.gov/2004629008 /// Tipuans who visited Ursúa just following the Itza conquest informed him that Tipu constituted two towns [ie Tipuj, Baltok?] of about 400 persons in all—not including a small population of Muzules in the forest toward the east. /v Jones 333 no 78 /PATRONATO,237,R.1,N.11 /// Though mission towns est and abandoned in southern Hon as late as 1724 /v Graham 195 /v Jones C 420 /xxx</ref>

